SIMPLE: fraudulent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fraudulent
<hw>Fraud"u*lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fraudulentus</ets>, fr. <ets>fraus</ets>, <ets>fraudis</ets>,
fraud: cf. F. <ets>fraudulent</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Using
fraud; tricky; deceitful; dishonest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Characterized by, founded on, or proceeding from,
fraud; <as>as, a <ex>fraudulent</ex> bargain</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He, with serpent tongue, . . . ⟦br⟧
His <qex>fraudulent</qex> temptation thus began.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Obtained or performed by artifice; <as>as,
<ex>fraudulent</ex> conquest</as>.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Deceitful; fraudful; guileful; crafty; wily;
cunning; subtle; deceiving; cheating; deceptive; insidious; treacherous;
dishonest; designing; unfair.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fraudulently</ent>⟦br⟧
